ers/cybersecurity/iec-62443.jsp","description":"Practical implementation guide for security zoning."},{"title":"Yokogawa Security Architecture White Paper","url":"https://www.yokogawa.com/library/resources/white-papers/industrial-security/","description":"Case study on mapping components to security contexts."}]},{"id":"KA3","title":"Secure Integration Testing","description":"Validation of component interactions under security constraints (e.g., firewall rules, role-based access). Identifies conflicts before production deployment.","related_links":[{"title":"MITRE ICS ATT&CK Evaluation","url":"https://attack.mitre.org/versions/v10/matrices/ics/","description":"Framework for testing ICS component integration security."},{"title":"Belden ICS Security Test Guide","url":" https://www.belden.com/hubfs/resources/guides/ICS-Cybersecurity-Testing-Guide.pdf","description":"Step-by-step guide for security testing ICS integrations."}]},{"id":"KA4","title":"Patch Management Coordination","description":"Process to synchronize patches across integrated components without disrupting operations. Addresses SG-3's requirement for maintainable security.","related_links":[{"title":"Siemens ICS Patch Management Guide","url":" https://assets.new.siemens.com/siemens/assets/api/uuid:9d30e5d2-9e6e-4586-8d34-68400d716e23/version:1616512439/simatic-ics-patch-management.pdf","description":"Vendor-specific patch management methodology."},{"title":"CISA ICS Patch Management","url":"https://www.cisa.gov/uscert/ics/advisories","description":"Authoritative source for ICS patch advisories."}]}],"name":"Security hardening guidelines","description":"A process shall be employed to create product user documentation that includes guidelines for hardening the product when installing and maintaining the product. The guidelines shall include, but are not limited to, instructions, rationale and recommendations for the following: a) integration of the product, including third-party components, with its produc